Basics:

C-x C-f - open file
C-x k bufname <RET> - kill buffer
C-x C-s - save
C-g - cancel partially typed or accidental command 
C-c r - rename file

Macros:


C-x ( - start define a keyboard macro - basically records what you do, so do exactly what you want your macro to do. 
C-x ) - end the definition of the keyboard macro 
C-x e - executes the keyboard macro.
C-u 15 C-x e - execute macro 15 times
C-u 0 C-x e - execute macro indefinitely
